# ✅ FRONTEND (React)

## 6️⃣ Read CSRF token from cookie

```js
function getCookie(name) {
  return document.cookie
    .split("; ")
    .find(row => row.startsWith(name + "="))
    ?.split("=")[1];
}
```

***

## 7️⃣ Send CSRF token with request

```js
fetch("http://localhost:4000/refresh", {
  method: "POST",
  credentials: "include", // IMPORTANT
  headers: {
    "X-CSRF-Token": getCookie("csrfToken")
  }
});
```

✅ Browser sends refresh cookie\
✅ React sends CSRF header\
✅ Server validates both

***

# 🚫 WHY THIS BLOCKS ATTACKS

### Attacker website CANNOT:

❌ Read cookies from another domain\
❌ Read CSRF token\
❌ Set custom headers cross‑site

### Legit app CAN:

✅ Read CSRF token\
✅ Send correct header\
✅ Pass validation

